author: Veronica Rocha
title: Body found on 101 Freeway near Thousand Oaks - LA Times
text:
Veronica Rocha .
The discovery was reported by drivers about 7:17 a.m. north of Rancho Road on the freeway, said Marco Marin, a spokesman for the CHP in Moorpark. Drivers reported seeing an object wrapped in blanket or some type of material, he said. 
When officers arrived, they found the man’s body, Marin said. The man is believed to be 67 years old. 
Authorities think a car was involved in the incident, but they don’t if the man was dumped on the freeway or hit by a passing vehicle, he said. 
The CHP is investigating, Marin said. 
Authorities closed a freeway lane as CHP officers collected evidence and waited for the coroner’s to arrive. They expected the lane to be closed for two hours.
